  "response": "IIFT (Indian Institute of Foreign Trade) Delhi is a well-respected institution for international business and trade management education, but it is generally considered to have a lower reputation compared to the prestigious IIMs (Indian Institutes of Management).\n\nKey points about IIFT's reputation:\n\n1. Specialization\n- IIFT is specifically focused on international business and trade\n- IIMs are broader management institutes with more diverse programs\n\n2. Ranking\n- IIMs are typically ranked higher in national management education rankings\n- IIFT is well-regarded but not at the same tier as top IIMs like Ahmedabad, Bangalore, and Calcutta\n\n3. Placements\n- IIMs generally offer higher average and median salary packages\n- IIFT has good placements, especially in international trade and export-import sectors\n\n4. Admission Difficulty\n- IIMs are more competitive and challenging to get into\n- IIFT has a relatively lower cut-off and entrance exam difficulty\n\n5. Brand Value\n- IIMs have a more established and globally recognized brand\n- IIFT is respected but has a more niche reputation\n\nWhile IIFT is a good institution, it is not considered equivalent to top-tier IIMs in overall management education reputation.",
